snippet: Ms. Boxer, a California Democrat who has served in the Senate since 1993, says in a video interview with a grandson, “I want to come home to the state that I love.”
abstract: Sen Barbara Boxer, Democrat of California, says she will not seek re-election, ending 30-year career in Congress; decision was broadly expected and is unlikely to change battle for Senate control.

byline.contributor: Jonathan Martin and Jeremy W. Peters contributed reporting from Washington.

lead_paragraph: Ms. Boxer, a California Democrat who has served in the Senate since 1993, says in a video interview with a grandson, “I want to come home to the state that I love.”

headline.main: Boxer Says She Won’t Seek Re-election to Senate in California in 2016
headline.print_headline: Boxer Says She Won’t Seek Re-election to Senate in California in 2016
